    <div class="rich-text-content richTextTealiumTracker " componentDetails="46EBF6A0-8911-40E4-96BA-19FD1A1EC7A3|Rich Text" id="46ebf6a0-8911-40e4-96ba-19fd1a1ec7a3">
        <p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">Our Privacy Policy</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>(last updated<span style="color: #000000;">&nbsp;January 21, 2026</span>) ) </strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">Brother International Corporation and its subsidiary company Brother Industries (U.S.A.) (&ldquo;Brother&rdquo;, &ldquo;we,&rdquo; or &ldquo;us&rdquo;) are committed to respecting and protecting your privacy. We know that the privacy of personal information is an important concern to our customers.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">This Privacy Policy (&ldquo;Privacy Policy&rdquo;) covers information that is collected through Brother websites, including <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://www.brother-usa.com/" target="_blank" class="link link-external">www.brother-usa.com</a>, <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://www.brothermobilesolutions.com/" target="_blank" class="link link-external">www.brothermobilesolutions.com</a>, <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://brotherdtg.com/" target="_blank" class="link link-external">https://brotherdtg.com</a>, and <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://www.ibroidery.com/" target="_blank" class="link link-external">www.ibroidery.com</a>, to which it is linked (&ldquo;Sites&rdquo;) and to the use of our products and/or services (&ldquo;Services&rdquo;). This Privacy Policy is a part of, and is incorporated into, any Terms of Service between you and Company which are applicable to our products and/or Services or Terms of Use when visiting our Sites. This Privacy Policy and such applicable Terms of Service or Terms of Use (together, the &ldquo;Agreement&rdquo;) comprise the entire agreement and understanding between you and Brother with respect to your access to and use of the Sites and Services.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><a href="//privacy.trustarc.com/privacy-seal/validation?rid=ec0be97b-12d7-465d-8d62-a4423cb6a3fc" target="_blank" class="link"><img style="border: none;" src="//hostedseal.trustarc.com/privacy-seal/seal?rid=ec0be97b-12d7-465d-8d62-a4423cb6a3fc" alt="TRUSTe" loading="lazy"><span class="sr-only">(Opens in a new tab)</span></a></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">This statement describes (i) the types of Personal Information we collect on the Sites and Services, (ii) how we use and protect the information, and (iii) to whom we disclose such information.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">PLEASE REVIEW THIS PRIVACY POLICY REGULARLY. By using the Sites and the Services or providing your Personal Information (as defined below) to Brother, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree to this Privacy Policy, you should not use the Sites, the Services, or provide your Personal Information to Brother. To the extent any provision of this Privacy Policy conflicts with the Terms of Service or Terms of Use applicable to the Services or Sites, respectively, then the applicable provision of the Terms of Service or Terms of use shall govern, except as to the extent (if any) otherwise expressly set forth in either this Privacy Policy or the Terms of Service or Terms of Use.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Collection of Personal Information</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">The following is a description of our data collection practices, including the personal information we collect, the sources of that information, the purposes for which we collect information, and whether we disclose that information to external parties.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Personal Information is any data that can be used to identify an individual.</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Personal Information</span>: The Personal Information that you may be asked to provide when creating an account, registering, utilizing the Sites or Services, leaving a product review, contacting customer support, or completing a transaction, may include, but not be limited to, your first and last name, mailing address (including ZIP code), e-mail address, username, billing contact information, and telephone.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Sensitive Information</span>: We may collect sensitive information including but not limited to gender, race, financials, and account login.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Payment Information</span>: When purchasing the Services or products online, you will be asked to provide payment information.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Social Media</span>: We collect your social media handle and basic account information when you interact with our services through social media.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Numerical Identifier</span>: We collect a unique numerical identifier which is automatically assigned to you by a first-party cookie when you use our Site, to identify you, provide our Services, keep you logged in to our Site, prevent fraud, and provide you with targeted information and offers.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Geolocation Data</span>: We may collect certain information about your access to and use of the Sites and the Services, such as the name of the Internet service provider and the Internet Protocol (IP) address through which you access the Internet, the dates and times that you access the Sites, and the Services, the pages that you view while at the Sites, information on how you interact with the Sites, and the Internet address of the website from which you linked to the Sites. Information regarding your computer system configuration and operating system is also gathered. This information is used by us to help analyze trends, enhance your experience on the Sites, send targeted advertisements, and to improve and administer the Services.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">You may opt-out of location-based services at any time by editing this setting at the device level or by submitting your request through the <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://brother-privacy.my.onetrust.com/webform/ff262f29-98ea-4e39-8ad9-53d4300405ce/860292b1-11bc-4958-b104-0b9e5e6205bb" target="_blank" class="link link-external">Privacy Portal</a>.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Commercial Information</span>: Brother and its affiliates may also collect information from and about your use of our products and the devices connected to the products including, but not limited to, the printer model, serial number, Device ID, the device location, usage data and operating information (collectively, &ldquo; Device Data&rdquo;). Our collection of Device Data is enabled by the software embedded in our products. You may opt-out of such collection by following the instructions in the End User License Agreement for the software. We use this information to monitor your use and the effectiveness of our Services, to identify you, and to provide you with targeted information and offers.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Testimonials</span>: We also display personal testimonials of customers on our Sites in addition to other endorsements. If you wish to update or delete your testimonial, please submit your request through the <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://brother-privacy.my.onetrust.com/webform/ff262f29-98ea-4e39-8ad9-53d4300405ce/860292b1-11bc-4958-b104-0b9e5e6205bb" target="_blank" class="link link-external">Privacy Portal</a>.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Promotional Materials</span>: If you receive newsletters or promotional e-mails from us, we may collect additional information about you through the use of and interaction with customized links or similar technologies to determine whether the e-mail was opened and for how long, and which links were utilized by you, in order to provide you more focused e-mail communications or other information. We may also use third party service providers for these data collection and delivery activities.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Use of Personal Information</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Provision of Services</span>: Brother may use your Personal Information to deliver and provide the Services you request, provide you with more effective customer service, to improve the Sites and the Services, and to make the Sites easier to use by eliminating the need for you to repeatedly enter the same information, or by customizing the Sites and Services to your preferences or interests, among other uses.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Registration Information</span>: We use your registration information to validate users, manage subscriptions, recall user settings (address book etc.) deliver Services, support, and improve the Services, and for our internal process evaluations. You may abandon registration at any time before completing the registration process.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Promotional Purposes</span>: With regard to Personal Information that is collected during the registration process from our users, upon completion of the registration process, user will receive email correspondence which provides the user the option not to receive communications from Brother regarding its Services and other product information. If you do not wish to receive such communications, you may opt-out or unsubscribe per this email. We present the OPT-OUT option to users in all marketing communications, except for system or service notifications, such as receipts, confirmation emails and customer service updates that are considered necessary to provide the Services to you.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Processing Payments</span>: The payment information that you provide when purchasing products or the Services is used only to facilitate payments and transactions.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">Surveys and Contests: Occasionally we may invite you to participate in surveys or contests. Participation in these surveys or contests is completely voluntary and the user therefore has a choice of whether or not to disclose Personal Information. The requested Personal Information usually includes contact information (such as name and shipping address), and demographic information (such as zip code), but the specific Personal Information collected in any survey may vary. Personal Information will be used by the contest or survey sponsors to notify the winners and award prizes and as otherwise provided in the applicable contest rules. You should carefully review the rules of each survey or contest in which you participate, as they may contain additional important information about Brother&rsquo;s or a sponsor&rsquo;s use of your Personal Information. To the extent that the terms and conditions of such rules concerning the treatment of your Personal Information conflict with this Privacy Policy, the terms and conditions of such rules shall control. We will not share the Personal Information you provide through a contest or survey with other third parties unless we give you prior notice and choice.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Social Media</span>: We use data collected through social media to improve our services, respond to your requests or complaints, and send information and advertisements to you.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">SMS Messages</span>: If you opt in to receive SMS messages from Brother, whether as delivery status updates or for marketing, you consent to us retaining and using the telephone number you provide for such purposes. We may use third party service providers to deliver such messages, but we do not share any consumer phone number or consent with such parties or any other parties for marketing or promotional purposes.&nbsp; Messaging and data rates may apply.&nbsp; You may opt out of receiving such messages by replying STOP, END or a similar instruction in response to such message or by updating your SMS Communication Preferences through your Brother account (<a href="https://www.brother-usa.com/myaccount/home" class="link link-external">www.brother-usa.com/myaccount/home</a>).&nbsp; Even if you opt-out of receiving SMS messages from us, we will retain your phone number and opt-in consent to protect our legal rights in accordance with applicable law unless and until we receive a &ldquo;delete my information&rdquo; request from you, if allowed under the laws of the jurisdiction in which you reside.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Consolidated User Data</span>: Brother may combine your Personal Information with data collected about your activity on our Sites and Services using Tracking Technologies, Device Data, and, if you register for an account, your registration information (the &ldquo;Consolidated User Data&rdquo;). We will use and share your Consolidated User Data for the purposes described elsewhere in this Privacy Policy and for the purpose of customizing your user experience on the Sites and Services by targeting advertisements, offerings, and content to your interests. Brother will use your Consolidated User Data on the Sites, Services, and applications, and not for purposes of tracking your activity on the Internet.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">User Preferences</span>: We may use your information to analyze your actual or likely preferences through a series of computer processes. On some occasions, we may add our observations to your internal profile. We use this information to gauge and develop our marketing activities, measure the appeal and effectiveness of our services, applications, and tools, and to provide you with targeted information, advertisements, and offers.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Disclosure and Sharing of Your Personal Information</strong></p>
<p>Brother may disclose user Personal Information in the following ways:</p>
<p>&bull; To comply with any law, regulation, or litigation; or,</p>
<p>&bull; To protect and defend the property rights of Company and its affiliates; or,</p>
<p>&bull; To act in urgent circumstances to protect the personal safety of any officer, director, employee, consultant, agent or representative of Company, any user of Company products or services including without limitation the Site and the Services, or any member of the public; or,</p>
<p>&bull; For reasons of national security, law enforcement or other issues of public importance.</p>
<p>&bull; In the event Company goes through a business transition or transaction, such as a merger, acquisition by another company, or sale of all or a portion of its assets, in which case user Personal Information will likely be among the assets transferred. You will be notified via email and/or prominent notice on our Web site for 30 days of any such change in ownership or control of your Personal Information.</p>
<p>&bull; We may also disclose your Personal Information to any other third party with your prior consent.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">Brother may share your information with:</p>
<p>&bull; <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Service Providers</span> : Our contractors, service providers, and other third parties we use to support our business may have access to your information to help carry out the services they are performing for us, such as: creating, maintaining, hosting, and delivering of our Site and our Services; conducting marketing, handling payments, order fulfillment; administering contests; conducting research and analytics; gathering information you provide in connection with your inquiries; and customer service.</p>
<p>&bull; <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Partners </span>: Depending on the partnership, we may share certain information including contact information (at your direction), identification and demographic information, transactional information, user-generated content that you provide, research and feedback, device information and identifiers, connection and usage information, public and commercial information, and social media information. Partners may use your information pursuant to their own policies.</p>
<p>&bull; <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Social Media Networks</span> : We may share your information with social media networks for example, if you click on a Facebook &ldquo;like&rdquo; button on our Site, the &ldquo;like&rdquo; may appear on your Facebook account. Or you may choose to share information directly on these networks using plug-ins for sharing. To control this sharing of information, please review and adjust your privacy settings for the relevant social media network. Depending on your privacy settings and actions on such network, we may share contact information, identification and demographic information, user-generated content, device information and identifiers, connection and usage data, and social media information.</p>
<p>&bull; <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Advertisers, Advertising Networks, and Other Third Parties</span> : We may share information about how you use the Services and interact with content or ads to better tailor services, products, marketing, and advertising on our Services and on third-party platforms. To enable these purposes, we may share certain demographics information, device information and identifiers, connection and usage data, geolocation data, public and commercial information, and social media information.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Updating Your Personal Account Information</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">If you are a user who registers an account with us, you may amend or update inaccurate or incomplete Personal Account Information, request deletion of such Personal Account Information, or request that we no longer use it. If your Personal Information changes, it is your responsibility and obligation to update it within your Account. If you wish to change, review, delete or update your Personal Account Information, you can do so by logging onto your &ldquo;My Account&rdquo; page. You can access or update your Personal Account Information and communication preferences we have on file. If you require assistance in updating or accessing your Personal Account Information, or if you would like to request that your account be marked as inactive, please submit your request to <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.brother-usa.com/contact-us?srsltid=AfmBOorgLkjWeLnie1eGjq70qiW1p53tpgPK48J1AQFZvkg4a7bRs2AD#search" target="_blank" class="link link-external">Brother Customer Service</a>.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Security of Your Personal Information</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">We are committed to protecting the security of your Personal Information. We use a variety of security technologies and procedures to help protect your Personal Information from unauthorized access, use or disclosure. For example, we store the Personal Information you provide to us on computer servers with limited access by others. When you transmit sensitive Personal Information (such as a credit card number) over the Internet, this information is transmitted through the use of Secure Socket Layer (SSL) encryption or other technologies. The Personal Information that you provide to Company in connection with registering as a user of the Site or the Services (such as your name and e-mail address) is protected in several ways. For example, your access to your registration information is available through a password and a unique customer ID which is a valid e-mail address provided by you. This password is encrypted. We recommend that you do not divulge your password to anyone. In addition, your registration information resides on secure servers accessible to only selected Company personnel. Company encrypts your Personal Information and strives to prevent unauthorized parties from viewing such information when it is transmitted to Company. We utilize security data security methods appropriate to the risks presented. No method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage, is 100% secure, however. Therefore, we cannot guarantee its absolute security. If you have any questions about security on our Web site, please submit your request through <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.brother-usa.com/contact-us?srsltid=AfmBOorgLkjWeLnie1eGjq70qiW1p53tpgPK48J1AQFZvkg4a7bRs2AD#search" target="_blank" class="link link-external">Brother Customer Service</a>.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">We will retain and use your Personal Information as disclosed in this policy and otherwise as reasonably necessary to comply with our legal obligations.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Tracking Technologies</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">We and our marketing partners, affiliates, or analytics or service providers, use technologies such as cookies, beacons, tags, scripts, or similar technologies to analyze trends, administer the Sites, track users&rsquo; movements around the Sites, and to gather demographic information about our user base as a whole. We may receive reports based on the use of these technologies by these companies on an individual and aggregated basis.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">One of the primary purposes of cookies is to help the Sites recall your information about you to deliver relevant content and ease navigation when you return to the Sites. Users can control the use of cookies at the individual browser level. If you reject cookies, you may still use our Sites and Services, but your ability to use some features or areas of the Sites and Services may be limited.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">In addition to cookies, the Site gathers certain information about users automatically that is stored in log files. This information includes IP/Internet address of your computer, your browser version, referring URLs and general web visitor information used by our web traffic reporting tools. This information may be linked to your registration information, and your navigation around the Sites may be tracked. We use this information to understand how the Sites are being used so that we can improve the Sites and offer appropriate products and services to our customers.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">We use clear gifs in our HTML-based emails to count traffic from users who link to the Sites from the e-mails or determine readership statistics. This allows us to gauge the effectiveness of certain communications and the effectiveness of our marketing campaigns.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">We also use Local Storage Objects (LSOs) such as HTML5 and Flash to store content information and preferences. Third parties with whom we partner to provide certain features on our Sites or display advertising based upon your Web browsing activity use HTML 5 to collect and store information. Various browsers may offer their own management tools for removing HTML5 LSOs.&nbsp; <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://www.macromedia.com/support/documentation/en/flashplayer/help/settings_manager.html#117118" target="_blank" class="link link-external">Learn how to manage privacy and storage settings for Flash cookies</a>.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">We partner with a third party to either display advertising on our Sites or manage our advertising on other sites. Our third party partner may use technologies such as cookies to gather information about your activities on our Sites and other sites in order to provide you advertising based upon your browsing activities and interests. If you wish to not have this information used for the purpose of serving you interest-based ads, <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://optout.aboutads.info/" target="_blank" class="link link-external">you may opt-out</a>. (or <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://www.youronlinechoices.eu/" target="_blank" class="link link-external">if located in the European Union</a>). Please note this does not opt you out of being served ads. You will continue to receive generic ads.</p>
<p><strong><span>Personalized Advertising and Retargeting</span></strong></p>
<p><span>We partner with <strong>RTB House</strong>&nbsp;to provide you with personalized advertising based on your browsing activity and interests. To achieve this, we allow RTB House to place tracking technologies (such as cookies, pixels, or tags) on our website.</span></p>
<p><strong><span>What data is collected?</span></strong><span>&nbsp;These technologies allow RTB House to collect information about your interaction with our website, such as pages visited, products viewed, and items added to your shopping cart.&nbsp;This data is tied to a unique online identifier (such as a cookie ID) assigned to your device.</span></p>
<p><strong><span>How to Opt-Out</span></strong><span>&nbsp;If you do not wish to receive personalized ads from RTB House, you can use the following mechanisms:</span></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0cm; list-style-type: disc;">
    <li><strong><span>Direct Opt-Out:</span></strong><span>&nbsp;You can opt out of RTB House&rsquo;s tracking and personalized ads by clicking the "Opt-out" button in the RTB House Privacy Center:&nbsp;<a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://optout.rtbhouse.com/" target="_blank" title="https://optout.rtbhouse.com/" class="link link-external">https://optout.rtbhouse.com/</a>.</span></li>
    <li><strong><span>Industry Opt-Out:</span></strong><span>&nbsp;RTB House is a member of the Network Advertising Initiative (NAI).&nbsp;You can use the NAI opt-out tool to opt out of seeing personalized ads:&nbsp;<a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://thenai.org/how-to-opt-out/" target="_blank" title="https://thenai.org/how-to-opt-out/" class="link link-external">https://thenai.org/how-to-opt-out/</a>.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span>Find more information on RTB House's technologies here: <a href="https://www.rtbhouse.com/privacy-center" class="link link-external">https://www.rtbhouse.com/privacy-center</a> </span></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Use of Google Analytics</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">We use Google Analytics, a web analytics service provided by Google LLC (&ldquo;<strong>Google</strong>&rdquo;), to track and monitor how you use our Sites. In connection with use of Google Analytics, we use cookies to distinguish unique users by assigning a randomly generated client ID that is used to monitor and calculate visitor, session and campaign data for the Sites analytics report. We may also implement Google Analytics Demographics and Interest Reporting, a feature of Google Analytics Advertising, to help us understand the demographics and interests of our Sites&rsquo; users. In connection with use of Google Analytics Advertising, our Sites and third-party vendors, including Google, use first-party cookies (such as the Google Analytics cookie) or other first-party identifiers, and third-party cookies (such as Google advertising cookies) or other third-party identifiers together.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">For more information about how Google handles your information, please see <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://www.google.com/policies/privacy/partners" target="_blank" class="link link-external">www.google.com/policies/privacy/partners</a>.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">If you would like to prevent your data from being collected and processed by Google Analytics, you can opt-out from Google Analytics by <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout/" target="_blank" class="link link-external">downloading and installing the Google Analytics&rsquo; Opt-out Add-on</a>.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Links to Other Web Sites</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">The Sites may contain links to third party websites. This Privacy Policy applies solely to the Sites, the Services, and to the Personal Information collected. You acknowledge and agree that Company is not responsible for the privacy practices or the content of third party websites, for your use of any third party websites, or for any intended or unintended consequences of such use. We encourage you to carefully read the privacy statement of any Web site you visit. Please understand that some sites provide geographic choices when you enter the Site. Upon selecting a geographic area, however, you may be redirected to a different site, with a different privacy policy.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Children</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">The Sites and Services are intended for general use audiences and are not directed to children under the age of 13. Brother does not knowingly collect, disclose or use any Personal Information of individuals under 13 years of age. If we become aware that any user under the age of 13 has provided Personal Information to us, we will immediately delete such information.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>International Visitors</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">The Sites and Services are hosted in the United States and all data collected from them are stored and processed in the United States. If you are visiting the Sites or using the Services from a non-US country that has privacy laws different from the United States, you understand and agree that Brother may collect, maintain, and process your data in the United States.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">To facilitate our operations, we may transfer, store and process your Personal Information (as defined below) in jurisdictions other than where you live, including in the United States. Laws in these countries may differ from the laws applicable to your country of residence. For instance, if you are a European Economic Area (EEA) data subject and your Personal Information is shared with our affiliates, partners, or third-party service providers acting on our behalf outside of the EEA, then it is done so pursuant to necessary means to ensure an adequate level of protection.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">Brother International Corporation and its subsidiary company Brother Industries (U.S.A.), Inc. (collectively &ldquo;Brother&rdquo;) complies with the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (EU-U.S. DPF), the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF, and the Swiss-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (Swiss-U.S. DPF) as set forth by the U.S. Department of Commerce. Brother has certified to the U.S. Department of Commerce that it adheres to the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework Principles (EU-U.S. DPF Principles) with regard to the processing of personal data received from the European Union in reliance on the EU-U.S. DPF and from the United Kingdom (and Gibraltar) in reliance on the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF. Brother certified to the U.S. Department of Commerce that it adheres to the Swiss-U.S. Data Privacy Framework Principles (Swiss-U.S. DPF Principles) with regard to the processing of personal data received from Switzerland in reliance on the Swiss-U.S. DPF. If there is any conflict between the terms in this privacy policy and the EU-U.S. DPF Principles and/or the Swiss-U.S. DPF Principles, the Principles shall govern. To learn more about the Data Privacy Framework (DPF) program, and to view our certification, please visit <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/" target="_blank" class="link link-external">https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/</a>.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">Brother is responsible for the processing of personal data it receives, under the Data Privacy Framework, and subsequent transfers to a third party acting as an agent on its behalf. Brother complies with the Data Privacy Framework Principles for all onward transfers of personal data from the EU, United Kingdom, and Switzerland, including the onward transfer liability provisions.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">The Federal Trade Commission has jurisdiction over Brother&rsquo;s compliance with the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (EU-U.S. DPF) and the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF, and the Swiss-US Data Privacy Framework (Swiss-U.S. DPF). In certain situations, Brother may be required to disclose personal data in response to lawful requests by public authorities, including for the purpose of meeting national security or law enforcement requirements.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">In compliance with the EU-U.S. DPF and the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF and the Swiss-U.S. DPF, Brother commits to refer unresolved complaints concerning our handling of personal data received in reliance on the EU-U.S. DPF and the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF and the Swiss-U.S. DPF to Truste, an alternative dispute resolution provider based in the United States. If you do not receive timely acknowledgment of your DPF Principles-related complaint from us, or if we have not addressed your DPF Principles-related complaint to your satisfaction, please visit <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://feedback-form.truste.com/watchdog/request" target="_blank" class="link link-external">https://feedback-form.truste.com/watchdog/request</a>&nbsp;for more information or to file a complaint. The services of Truste are provided at no cost to you.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">Under certain conditions, more fully described on the Data Privacy Framework website at <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/framework-article/ANNEX-I-introduction" target="_blank" class="link link-external">https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/framework-article/ANNEX-I-introduction</a>, you may invoke binding arbitration when other dispute resolution procedures have been exhausted.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">In all cases where Brother transfers personal information to a third party acting as a controller, Brother will comply with the Notice and Choice Principles. Brother will enter into a contract with the third-party controller that provides that such data may only be processed for limited and specified purposes consistent with the consent provided by you and that the recipient will provide the same level of protection as the Principles and will notify Brother if it makes a determination that it can no longer meet this obligation. The contract also provides that when such a determination is made the third party controller will cease processing or takes other reasonable and appropriate steps to remediate.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">In all cases where Brother transfers personal data to a third party acting as an agent (processor for GDPR purposes), Brother will: (i) transfer such data only for limited and specified purposes; (ii) ascertain that the agent is obligated to provide at least the same level of privacy protection as is required by the Principles; (iii) take reasonable and appropriate steps to ensure that the agent effectively processes the personal information transferred in a manner consistent with the organization&rsquo;s obligations under the Principles; (iv) require the agent to notify Brother if it makes a determination that it can no longer meet its obligation to provide the same level of protection as is required by the Principles; (v) upon notice, including under (iv), take reasonable and appropriate steps to stop and remediate unauthorized processing; and (vi) provide a summary or a representative copy of the relevant privacy provisions of Brother&rsquo;s contract with that agent to the U.S. Department of Commerce upon request.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">When we transfer your information to third parties we comply with the requirements of the legal protections that cover your information. For example, when we perform an onward transfer of your information protected under the GDPR, we remain responsible for the processing of your personal information. For information subject to an onward transfer by us under the Data Privacy Framework, we will remain liable under the Data Privacy Framework Principles if a recipient of your protected personal information processes such personal information in a manner inconsistent with the Principles, unless we are able to prove that we are not responsible for the event giving rise to the damage.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Assignment</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">We reserve the right to transfer any and all information that we collect from users to a third party in the event of any merger, sale, joint venture, assignment, transfer or other disposition of all or any portion of Brother&rsquo;s assets or stock (including without limitation in connection with any bankruptcy or similar proceedings).</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Your Privacy Rights</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Right to Access Information</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">You have the right to request access to Personal Information collected about you and information regarding the source of that information, the purposes for which we collect it, and the third parties and service providers with whom we share it. To protect our customers&rsquo; Personal Information, we are required to verify your identity before we can act on your request.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Right to Request Deletion of Information</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">You have the right to request in certain circumstances that we delete any Personal Information that we have collected directly from you. To protect our customers&rsquo; Personal Information, we are required to verify your identity before we can act on your request. We may have a reason under the law why we do not have to comply with your request, or why we may comply with it in a more limited way than you anticipated. If we do, we will explain that to you in our response.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Right to Correct Inaccurate Information</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">You have the right to correct inaccurate Personal Information we have collected. To protect our customers&rsquo; Personal Information, we are required to verify your identity before we can act on your request.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Right to Opt-Out of Sale of Personal Information</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">Brother does not sell your Personal Information; however, to the extent that we have third party interest-based advertising on our Site, <a class="link" href="http://optout.aboutads.info/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">you may opt-out</a>. (or <a class="link" href="http://www.youronlinechoices.eu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">if located in the European Union</a>).</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Right to Information Regarding Participation in Data Sharing for Financial Incentives</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">We may run promotions from time to time whereby we incentivize a consumer to share certain pieces of information with us; for example, we may offer a one-time discount if consumers sign up for our email marketing list. Participation in these incentives is voluntary and you may opt out of the data sharing at any time.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>California's Shine the Light Act Rights</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">Residents of California also have the right to request information regarding third parties to whom the company has disclosed certain categories of Personal Information during the preceding year for the third parties&rsquo; direct marketing purposes.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>How to Submit a Request</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">You may submit a request to exercise your rights through one of the following means:</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">1) By filling out the form located at: <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://brother-privacy.my.onetrust.com/webform/ff262f29-98ea-4e39-8ad9-53d4300405ce/860292b1-11bc-4958-b104-0b9e5e6205bb" target="_blank" class="link link-external">Privacy Portal</a>.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">2) By calling us at 1-855-996-0289, Monday through Friday, during the hours of 6:00 AM to 3:00 PM Pacific Time.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">We will provide a response to your request within forty-five (45) days.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">Before complying with a Consumer Data Rights Request, we will first contact you to verify your identity.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">You may also designate someone else to make a request on your behalf. To protect your information, we will ask for a signed permission from you authorizing the other person to submit a request on your behalf. We will contact you to verify your identity before we respond to your authorized agent&rsquo;s request.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Company Contact Information</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">If you have questions regarding this Privacy Policy, please submit your request to <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection" class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="d2a2a0bba4b3b1ab92b0a0bda6bab7a0fcb1bdbf">[email&#160;protected]</a>.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">You may also contact us at Brother International Corporation, Attn: Legal Department, Data Privacy, 200 Crossing Blvd, Bridgewater, NJ 08807.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">In your correspondence, please ask your question in detail. We will investigate your question or concern and will use commercially reasonable efforts to promptly provide an answer or otherwise to determine and remedy the problem. We will reply to you by the same method by which you contacted us.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Changes to the Privacy Policy</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the &ldquo;Last Updated&rdquo; date at the top of the Privacy Policy. We encourage you to periodically review this Privacy Policy to stay informed about our policies and procedures concerning privacy, including how we are helping to protect the Personal Information we collect. Your continued use of the Site and Services constitutes your agreement to and acceptance of this Privacy Policy and any updates. You will be deemed to have been made aware of, and will be subject to, any changes to the Privacy Policy immediately upon the posting of notice of such changes on the Site.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>SMS Messaging Privacy Policy</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">We are committed to protecting your privacy. This SMS Messaging Privacy Policy (&ldquo;Policy&rdquo;) governs how we collect and use information about you in relation to text message marketing program(s) (the &ldquo;Messaging Service&rdquo;), which we make available to you through a third-party service provider.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">By using the Messaging Service, you agree to the terms of this Policy. Brother reserves the right, in our sole discretion, to modify or change this Policy at any time with or without prior notice to you. The date of the last update will be posted at the top of this Policy for your convenience. This Policy, and any changes, are effective as soon as posted and supersede any prior Policies. Your continued use of the Messaging Service following the posting of any changes to the Policy constitutes your full acceptance of those changes.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Collection of Information</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">Through your use of the Messaging Service, we will receive Personal Information through our third-party service provider. &ldquo;Personal Information&rdquo; is information that individually identifies you, such as your mobile phone number you provided when signing up for the Messaging Service, any user or screen name that you select in connection with the Messaging Service, any comments or feedback regarding the Messaging Service that you send to us, or any other information that you choose to include in messages you send through the Messaging Service. When you send messages via the Messaging Service, we will also collect your messaging history and any information included in those messages.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">We may also collect Personal Information about you using cookies or similar technologies. Cookies are pieces of information that are stored by your browser on the hard drive or memory of your device. Cookies enable personalization of your experience on the Messaging Service (e.g., sending you personalized text messages such as shopping cart reminders).</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">If you participate in a contest, sweepstakes, research study, or email survey associated with the Messaging Service, we will collect basic contact information and any other information you choose to provide in connection with these activities. We will also collect your contact information if you contact us with questions about the Messaging Service or for customer service.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Use of Information</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">We use Personal Information to deliver, analyze, maintain and support the Messaging Service. We may also use Personal Information to enhance the Messaging Service features and customize and personalize your experiences on the Messaging Service. Additionally, we will use this information to send you text notifications (for your order, including abandoned checkout reminders), text marketing offers, and transactional texts, including requests for reviews from us.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Sharing of Information</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">Brother will not rent or sell your Personal Information to other companies or individuals unless we have your consent. We may use or disclose Personal Information in any of the following limited circumstances:</p>
<p>&bull; We have your consent.</p>
<p>&bull; We need to enforce our Terms of Service.</p>
<p>&bull; We provide such information to trusted businesses or persons for the sole purpose of processing Personal Information on our behalf or providing the Messaging Service to you. When this is done, it is subject to agreements that oblige those parties to process such information only on our instructions and in compliance with this Policy and appropriate confidentiality and security measures. If the third party fails to comply with our terms, Brother is not accountable in any way for any liability or reimbursement.</p>
<p>&bull; We provide Personal Information to a company controlled by, or under common control with, Brother for any purpose permitted by this Policy. &bull; We transfer Personal Information about you if Brother is, or its assets are, acquired by or merged with another company.</p>
<p>&bull; We believe disclosure of Personal Information is necessary or appropriate to: (i) comply with applicable law and legal processes; (ii) respond to requests from public and government authorities, including public and government authorities outside your country of residence; (iii) enforce a contract with us; (iv) protect our rights, privacy, safety, or property, and/or that of our affiliates, you or others; and (v) allow us to pursue available remedies or limit the damages that we may sustain. From time to time, we may share aggregate or de-identified information about use of the Messaging Service and such aggregated or de-identified information may be shared with any third party, including advertisers, promotional partners, and sponsors.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Protection of Information</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">Brother takes a variety of physical, technical, administrative, and organizational security measures based on the sensitivity of the information we collect to protect your Personal Information against accidental or unlawful destruction or accidental loss, alteration, unauthorized disclosure or access. Unfortunately, no online activity can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. You should note that in using the Messaging Service, your information will travel through third-party infrastructures which are not under our control (such as a third-party provider&rsquo;s SMS delivery platform or your carrier network). While we strive to protect your information against unauthorized use or disclosure, we cannot ensure or warrant the security of any information you provide. By using the Messaging Service, you agree that Brother is not liable for any unintentional disclosure.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Retention of Information</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">We retain your Personal Information for as long as you participate in the Messaging Service or as needed to comply with applicable legal obligations. We will also retain and use your Personal Information as necessary to resolve disputes, protect us and our customers, and enforce our agreements.</p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;"><strong>Choices and Controls</strong></p>
<p style="color: #000000; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15pt;">Consent to receive automated marketing text messages is not a condition of any purchase. You can opt-out of receiving further commercial text messages via the Messaging Service by responding to any of our text messages with any of the following replies: STOP, END, CANCEL, UNSUBSCRIBE, or QUIT. For more information, see our Mobile Messaging Terms and Conditions available at <a href="https://www.brother-usa.com/terms-of-use" class="link link-external">https://www.brother-usa.com/terms-of-use</a></p>
